This paper deals with computational social choice and the problem of predicting the winner of an election using algorithms. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.GT (Computational Social Choice). The paper also involves analyzing the performance of algorithms, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses lower and upper bounds, which is related to the sub-category of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper deals with practical scenarios, which falls under the sub-category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
